OL,7,FHe was taken to , where he suffered a
OL,8,Fcardiac arrest in the early hours of
OL,9,FTuesday 26 March, with his heart
OL,10,Fstopping for four minutes.JIt is
OL,11,Fbelieved Andy had developed sepsis,
OL,12,Fwhich then caused encephalitis and
OL,13,Fmeningitis. This resulted in
OL,14,Funrecoverable swelling on the brain.
OL,15,FAndy was moved to intensive care in a
OL,16,Fcritical condition, but on Wednesday
OL,17,F27 March, his wife was told he was
OL,18,Flikely to die. The family said their
OL,19,Fgoodbyes to him, and he passed away on
OL,20,FFriday.JHelen said: "It's been
OL,21,Fincredibly hard to come to terms with
OL,22,Fit. Well, we've not come to terms with
OL,23,Fit. This person was everything to our
OL,24,Ffamily, he did everything for our
OL,25,Fkids."
